Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following three stories:

  • I Hunted the World's Wildest Animals!
  • I Found the City Under the Sea!
  • I Was Tried by the Jury of Villains!

The issue also features the following small comic strip:

  • Moolah the Mystic

I Hunted the World's Wildest Animals

Fred Burke is one of the worlds greatest big game hunters; fighting and defeating animals such as elephants and lions. He was the informed of a strange island where he could fighter tougher and more dangerous beasts; interesting in this opportunity he listened to the man who told him exactly where the island would be. Fred Burke believes that he can defeat the worlds toughest animals, but has he met his match when he fights creatures from myth?

I Found the City Under the Sea

Ellery Jones always believe that there was some sort of underwater civilization waiting to be discovered. What he didn't expect is that he'd find a society of conquerors who've made Earth their next target! Can Ellery foil their plot or will Earth become a conquered land?

I Was Tried by the Jury of Villains

Tod Lamont was getting tired of reusing the same old villain for all of his detective novels, even if the public loved it! Planning to kill of the villain he soon finds himself on trial and the jury is a selection of histories greatest villains! Can Lamont prove his innocent or is he going to be facing a life sentence in this novel nightmare?

Moolah the Mystic

Moolah takes magic carpet lessons in an attempt to learn how to fly.
name: I Was Tried by the Jury of Villains!
The Bouncing Boy of Company B

description:
The Secret of the Empty Box

The Flash has always rocketed into jet action at the appearance of villainy! But, this time, the Fastest Man Alive is stopped by "The Secret of the Empty Box!"

The Coldest Man On Earth!

The first encounter between the Flash and criminal called Captain Cold resulted in a defeat for the World's Fastest Human! Under what fantastic circumstances would they meet again? and what new, ingenious trick would the Scarlet Speedster have to overcome to capture...The Coldest Man on Earth!

Also contained in this issue are a two-page comic article on the speed of light and a three-page story on a race between a stagecoach and a sailing ship in the mid-19th Century.
name: The Secret of the Empty Box! / The Coldest Man on Earth!

description:
Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following three stories:

  • I Met the First Martian!
  • I Died a Thousand Times!
  • I Built the Super-Cage!

It also features the following comic strip:

  • Binky Shows "How To Make New Friends"

I Met the First Martian

While on a plan with four other passengers, Victor Harte experiences a crash landing. Everyone survives the crash and a strange object known as a U.F.O. is found nearby the crash. Things begin to get strange when the survivors start seeing illusions and begin transforming into crystal statues!

I Died a Thousand Times

The great explorer, Bob Perry, is nearly killed in an accident. After his near-death experience he is invited to join a mysterious group known as the Lonely Adventurers Club; however, not all is as it seems when Bob realizes the club is able to predict accidents before they happen.

I Built the Super-Cage

The construction man, Brett, and his fellow workers are hired to construct a large holding device known as the super-cage. Nobody knows what the device is supposed to hold, not even Brett, and when they find out they might regret taking the job!

Binky Shows "How To Make New Friends"

Binky teachers the reader how to make new friends.
name: I Built the Super Cage!

description:
1. Cover by Ruben Moreira and Al Plastino.
  2. "The Girl in Superman's Past" written by Jerry Coleman, penciled by Ruben Moreira and inked by Al Plastino. When Lana Lang shows up in Metropolis, she and Lois Lane get into a competition for Superman's attention.
  3. Odd Newspaper Facts
  4. The New Lois Lane
  5. Jerry the Jitterbug
  6. Newspaper Talk
  7. Sleuths In Skirts
  8. Mrs Superman
  9. Ollie

The future title, "Superman's girlfriend Lois Lane" got a try out in issues #9 and #10 of Showcase, when Lois stepped in as the lead feature. The debut story in this issue, "The Girl in Superman's past" by writer Jerry Coleman and artist Al Plastino, introduced Lois Lane to Superman's old flame Lana Lang. After some initial friction, the two inquisitive women realized they had a common curiosity: the strange parallels between Clark Kent and Superman. Lois and Lana began a friendly competition to see which of them Superman liked more and set "traps" to test his preference. Their schemes became progressively more outlandish, but Superman could not be outwitted. Superman similarly played Lois and "Con" Conners off against each other to protect his identity in the story called, "The New Lois Lane", while Lois dreamed of being Superman's wife in "Mrs Superman."
name: The Girl in Superman's Past! / The New Lois Lane / Mrs. Superman
